{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780373179898,"sessionID":"ses_1797e0d22ffeXZXWmRS3UmbrPG","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_xp3Mp61tp0S1YeNLt5kCNXFS","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/references/smart_routing.md","offset":261,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/references/smart_routing.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n261: \n262: - Load only references needed for current intent + surface\n263: - Honor the WEBFLOW implementation trio contract on every WEBFLOW invocation\n264: - Use exact canonical file paths in playbook result YAML (never directory placeholders)\n265: - Load Motion.dev peer resources after the surface decision, not as a substitute\n266: - Cite surface + top-1 intent + loaded resource paths + verification command in your final answer\n267: \n268: ### DON'T\n269: \n270: - Load all of `webflow/` or all of `opencode/` indiscriminately (\"just in case\")\n271: - Treat MOTION_DEV as a surface (it's a peer resource category)\n272: - Load Go/NextJS/React Native resources (those live in the Barter fork)\n273: - Skip the implementation trio for WEBFLOW\n274: - Drop directory placeholders in playbook result YAML\n275: \n276: ---\n277: \n278: ## 10. RELATED RESOURCES\n279: \n280: - [`./stack_detection.md`](./stack_detection.md) — surface detection (WEBFLOW/OPENCODE/UNKNOWN) + OPENCODE language sub-detection\n281: - [`./phase_detection.md`](./phase_detection.md) — Phase 1/2/3 lifecycle and per-phase resource loading\n282: - `SKILL.md` §2 SMART ROUTING — operator-facing summary of this routing contract\n283: - Barter equivalent: `barter/.opencode/skills/sk-code/references/smart_routing.md` (different routing key — git-remote project — but same structural pattern)\n284: \n285: ---\n286: \n287: ## 11. MACHINE-READABLE ROUTER (replay / benchmark source)\n288: \n289: This is the single machine-readable projection of the prose Intent Model (§2) and the per-surface maps (§4 Webflow, §5 Motion.dev, §6 OpenCode). The prose sections above are the human-facing contract; this block is the byte-for-byte source a deterministic router-replay parses. Keep the two in sync: when a map row changes above, update the matching `RESOURCE_MAP` entry here.\n290: \n291: A drift guard (`.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/tests/sk-code-router-sync.vitest.ts`) keeps this block honest: it fails if any path here is missing on disk, if any routable `references/`/`assets/` doc stops being covered, or if an explicit full path named in the prose maps is absent here. Run it standalone with `npx vitest run skill-benchmark/tests/sk-code-router-sync.vitest.ts` from `.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts`.\n292: \n293: This projection is intentionally lossy in two documented ways the flat dictionary cannot express, both enforced by the prose contract and the surface-detection pseudocode in `SKILL.md` §2:\n294: \n295: - **No phase boosts.** The `+5` unambiguous-phase boost from the §2 scoring algorithm is not represented; every keyword carries unit weight here.\n296: - **No doc-only anti-signals.** The `sk-code -2 / sk-doc +3` anti-signals (§2) that route prose-only edits away from this skill are a pre-filter the flat model does not carry.\n297: \n298: ```python\n299: # Always-loaded routing preamble: every code task detects stack, detects phase,\n300: # consults the router, and applies the universal quality baseline before any\n301: # surface-specific resource. These are loaded on every route.\n302: DEFAULT_RESOURCE = [\n303:     \"references/stack_detection.md\",\n304:     \"references/phase_detection.md\",\n305:     \"references/smart_routing.md\",\n306:     \"references/universal/code_quality_standards.md\",\n307: ]\n308: \n309: INTENT_SIGNALS = {\n310:     \"IMPLEMENTATION\":     {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"implement\", \"build\", \"create\", \"feature\", \"component\", \"module\", \"authoring\"]},\n311:     \"CODE_QUALITY\":       {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"lint\", \"format\", \"quality gate\", \"naming\", \"standards\", \"code smell\"]},\n312:     \"DEBUGGING\":          {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"debug\", \"broken\", \"failing\", \"stack trace\", \"console error\", \"regression\"]},\n313:     \"VERIFICATION\":       {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"verify\", \"passing\", \"type-check\", \"alignment drift\", \"completion claim\"]},\n314:     \"TESTING\":            {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"unit test\", \"integration test\", \"coverage\", \"vitest\", \"pytest\", \"shellcheck\"]},\n315:     \"DEPLOYMENT\":         {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"deploy\", \"cdn\", \"wrangler\", \"minify\", \"staging\", \"production release\"]},\n316:     \"PERFORMANCE\":        {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"lighthouse\", \"core web vitals\", \"largest contentful\", \"pagespeed\", \"jank\", \"frame budget\"]},\n317:     \"ANIMATION\":          {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"transition\", \"gsap\", \"lenis\", \"carousel\", \"parallax\"]},\n318:     \"MOTION_DEV\":         {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"motion.dev\", \"motion-dev\", \"animate()\", \"inview\", \"scroll()\", \"cross-stack animation\"]},\n319:     \"FORMS\":              {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"form upload\", \"filepond\", \"field validation\", \"focus trap\"]},\n320:     \"VIDEO\":              {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"hls\", \"adaptive stream\", \"video player\"]},\n321:     \"HOOKS\":              {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"session-prime\", \"user-prompt-submit\", \"pre-tool-use\", \"post-tool-use\"]},\n322:     \"CONFIG\":             {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"jsonc\", \".json\", \".jsonc\", \"descriptor\", \"config schema\"]},\n323:     \"LANGUAGE_STANDARDS\": {\"weight\": 1, \"keywords\": [\"typescript\", \".ts\", \".tsx\", \"python\", \".py\", \"shell script\", \"bash\", \".sh\", \"commonjs\", \".cjs\", \".mjs\", \"docstring\"]},\n324: }\n325: \n326: RESOURCE_MAP = {\n327:     \"IMPLEMENTATION\": [\n328:         \"references/universal/multi_agent_research.md\",\n329:         \"references/webflow/implementation/implementation_workflows.md\",\n330:         \"references/webflow/implementation/async_patterns.md\",\n331:         \"references/webflow/implementation/observer_patterns.md\",\n332:         \"references/webflow/implementation/security_patterns.md\",\n333:         \"references/webflow/implementation/third_party_integrations.md\",\n334:         \"references/webflow/implementation/webflow_patterns.md\",\n335:         \"references/webflow/shared/dev_workflow.md\",\n336:         \"references/opencode/shared/universal_patterns.md\",\n337:         \"references/opencode/shared/code_organization.md\",\n338:         \"assets/opencode/checklists/agent_authoring.md\",\n339:         \"assets/opencode/checklists/command_authoring.md\",\n340:         \"assets/opencode/checklists/skill_authoring.md\",\n341:         \"assets/opencode/checklists/mcp_server_authoring.md\",\n342:         \"assets/opencode/checklists/spec_folder_authoring.md\",\n343:         \"assets/opencode/recipes/spec_folder_write.md\",\n344:         \"assets/universal/patterns/README.md\",\n345:         \"assets/webflow/integrations/README.md\",\n346:         \"assets/webflow/patterns/README.md\",\n347:         \"assets/webflow/templates/README.md\"\n348:     ],\n349:     \"CODE_QUALITY\": [\n350:         \"references/universal/code_quality_standards.md\",\n351:         \"references/universal/code_style_guide.md\",\n352:         \"references/webflow/shared/cross_language_rules.md\",\n353:         \"references/webflow/shared/enforcement.md\",\n354:         \"assets/opencode/checklists/universal_checklist.md\",\n355:         \"assets/opencode/checklists/javascript_checklist.md\",\n356:         \"assets/opencode/checklists/typescript_checklist.md\",\n357:         \"assets/opencode/checklists/python_checklist.md\",\n358:         \"assets/opencode/checklists/shell_checklist.md\",\n359:         \"assets/webflow/checklists/code_quality_checklist.md\"\n360:     ],\n361:     \"DEBUGGING\": [\n362:         \"references/universal/error_recovery.md\",\n363:         \"references/webflow/debugging/debugging_workflows.md\",\n364:         \"references/webflow/debugging/error_recovery.md\",\n365:         \"assets/universal/checklists/debugging_checklist.md\",\n366:         \"assets/webflow/checklists/debugging_checklist.md\"\n367:     ],\n368:     \"VERIFICATION\": [\n369:         \"references/webflow/verification/verification_workflows.md\",\n370:         \"references/opencode/shared/alignment_verification_automation.md\",\n371:         \"assets/universal/checklists/verification_checklist.md\",\n372:         \"assets/webflow/checklists/verification_checklist.md\",\n373:         \"assets/scripts/README.md\"\n374:     ],\n375:     \"TESTING\": [\n376:         \"assets/motion_dev/playbook_entries.md\"\n377:     ],\n378:     \"DEPLOYMENT\": [\n379:         \"references/webflow/deployment/cdn_deployment.md\",\n380:         \"references/webflow/deployment/minification_guide.md\",\n381:         \"references/webflow/deployment/webflow_staging_production.md\",\n382:         \"assets/webflow/scripts/README.md\"\n383:     ],\n384:     \"PERFORMANCE\": [\n385:         \"references/webflow/performance/cwv_remediation.md\",\n386:         \"references/webflow/performance/interaction_gated_loading.md\",\n387:         \"references/webflow/performance/resource_loading.md\",\n388:         \"references/webflow/performance/third_party.md\",\n389:         \"references/webflow/performance/webflow_constraints.md\",\n390:         \"references/webflow/verification/performance_checklist.md\",\n391:         \"references/webflow/implementation/performance_patterns.md\",\n392:         \"references/motion_dev/performance_and_pitfalls.md\",\n393:         \"assets/webflow/checklists/performance_loading_checklist.md\"\n394:     ],\n395:     \"ANIMATION\": [\n396:         \"references/webflow/implementation/animation_workflows.md\",\n397:         \"references/webflow/implementation/swiper_patterns.md\"\n398:     ],\n399:     \"MOTION_DEV\": [\n400:         \"references/motion_dev/quick_start.md\",\n401:         \"references/motion_dev/animate_and_timelines.md\",\n402:         \"references/motion_dev/scroll_and_gestures.md\",\n403:         \"references/motion_dev/integration_patterns.md\",\n404:         \"references/motion_dev/decision_matrix.md\",\n405:         \"assets/motion_dev/install_card.md\",\n406:         \"assets/motion_dev/snippets/README.md\"\n407:     ],\n408:     \"FORMS\": [\n409:         \"references/webflow/implementation/form_upload_workflows.md\",\n410:         \"references/webflow/implementation/focus_management.md\"\n411:     ],\n412:     \"VIDEO\": [\n413:         \"references/webflow/implementation/third_party_integrations.md\"\n414:     ],\n415:     \"HOOKS\": [\n416:         \"references/opencode/shared/hooks.md\"\n417:     ],\n418:     \"CONFIG\": [\n419:         \"references/opencode/config/style_guide.md\",\n420:         \"references/opencode/config/quality_standards.md\",\n421:         \"references/opencode/config/quick_reference.md\",\n422:         \"assets/opencode/checklists/config_checklist.md\"\n423:     ],\n424:     \"LANGUAGE_STANDARDS\": [\n425:         \"references/webflow/css/style_guide.md\",\n426:         \"references/webflow/css/quality_standards.md\",\n427:         \"references/webflow/css/quick_reference.md\",\n428:         \"references/webflow/css/patterns.md\",\n429:         \"references/webflow/html/style_guide.md\",\n430:         \"references/webflow/html/quality_standards.md\",\n431:         \"references/webflow/javascript/style_guide.md\",\n432:         \"references/webflow/javascript/quality_standards.md\",\n433:         \"references/webflow/javascript/quick_reference.md\",\n434:         \"references/opencode/javascript/style_guide.md\",\n435:         \"references/opencode/javascript/quality_standards.md\",\n436:         \"references/opencode/javascript/quick_reference.md\",\n437:         \"references/opencode/typescript/style_guide.md\",\n438:         \"references/opencode/typescript/quality_standards.md\",\n439:         \"references/opencode/typescript/quick_reference.md\",\n440:         \"references/opencode/python/style_guide.md\",\n441:         \"references/opencode/python/quality_standards.md\",\n442:         \"references/opencode/python/quick_reference.md\",\n443:         \"references/opencode/shell/style_guide.md\",\n444:         \"references/opencode/shell/quality_standards.md\",\n445:         \"references/opencode/shell/quick_reference.md\"\n446:     ],\n447: }\n448: ```\n449: \n450: ### Surface-aware loading (route-time)\n451: \n452: The router does NOT load the whole matched-intent union. After surface detection (§1, `stack_detection.md`), a route loads:\n453: \n454: - the always-loaded `DEFAULT_RESOURCE` preamble (stack/phase detection, the router, the universal quality baseline), plus\n455: - the surface-agnostic `references/universal/*` tier, plus\n456: - only the **detected surface's** slice (`references/<surface>/*`) for the matched intents, plus\n457: - the Motion.dev overlay (`references/motion_dev/*`) when a `MOTION_DEV` intent fires.\n458: \n459: It does not load the other surface's resources, and it defers `assets/*` (checklists, recipes, templates) to on-demand rather than the first slice. Within OpenCode it slices once more by the **detected language** (§1 sub-detection): a TypeScript task loads `references/opencode/typescript/*` plus the language-agnostic `references/opencode/shared/*`, not the Python, shell, config, or JavaScript folders. Webflow has no language sub-slice — a frontend task legitimately spans CSS, HTML, and JavaScript together. A task that genuinely spans both surfaces (mixed `.opencode/` and Webflow markers) keeps both surface slices; an `UNKNOWN` surface falls back to the preamble plus the universal tier and the Motion overlay only. This is what stops a routine single-surface task from pulling the full cross-surface set. The deterministic router-replay enforces the same rule, so the benchmark measures it.\n\n(End of file - total 459 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\n- Load only references needed for current intent + surface\n- Honor the WEBFLOW implementation trio contract on every WEBFLOW invocation\n- Use exact canonical file paths in playbook result YAML (never directory placeholders)\n- Load Motion.dev peer resources after the surface decision, not as a substitute\n- Cite surface + top-1 intent + loaded resource paths + verification command in your final answer\n\n### DON'T\n\n- Load all of `webflow/` or all of `opencode/` indiscriminately (\"just in case\")\n- Treat MOTION_DEV as a surface (it's a peer resource category)\n- Load Go/NextJS/React Native resources (those live in the Barter fork)\n- Skip the implementation trio for WEBFLOW\n- Drop directory placeholders in playbook result YAML\n\n---\n\n## 10. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n- [`./stack_detection.md`](./stack_detection.md) — surface detection (WEBFLOW/OPENCODE/UNKNOWN) + OPENCODE language sub-detection","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/references/smart_routing.md","time":{"start":1780373179888,"end":1780373179896}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_04711fd250ccd945016a1e56bbcd6881918b6096819496a4c7"}},"id":"prt_e8682cdad001Z4lVkLSkaeYUuN","sessionID":"ses_1797e0d22ffeXZXWmRS3UmbrPG","messageID":"msg_e8682affc0017thL0dq1w8C6yZ"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780373179955,"sessionID":"ses_1797e0d22ffeXZXWmRS3UmbrPG","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_wSS8mi9iF1J9PqJnGyDHFXNZ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/02--language-sub-detection/004-opencode-typescript.md","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/02--language-sub-detection/004-opencode-typescript.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"LS-001: OPENCODE TypeScript Sub-Detection\"\n3: description: \"Verify that within OPENCODE surface, TypeScript file extensions trigger loading of typescript/* references (not python, shell, or config).\"\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # LS-001: OPENCODE TypeScript Sub-Detection\n7: \n8: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n9: \n10: This scenario verifies the language sub-detection layer within OPENCODE. When the target file extension is `.ts`, `.tsx`, `.mts`, or `.d.ts`, sk-code MUST load the `references/opencode/typescript/*` set and corresponding `assets/opencode/checklists/typescript_checklist.md`, while excluding python, shell, and config sub-language references.\n11: \n12: Sub-detection rules are defined in SKILL.md lines 78-90 and `references/stack_detection.md:50-62`.\n13: \n14: ## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n15: \n16: **Realistic user request**: A maintainer wants to harden the executor-config parser to throw early when an invalid model is supplied for cli-codex.\n17: \n18: **Exact prompt**:\n19: ```\n20: Refactor the parseExecutorConfig function in .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts to throw on missing model when type is cli-codex.\n21: ```\n22: \n23: **Expected detection**:\n24: - Surface: `OPENCODE`\n25: - Sub-language: `TYPESCRIPT` (target file `.ts`)\n26: \n27: **Expected references loaded** (must be EXACTLY this set, no more, no less from the language tier):\n28: - `references/opencode/typescript/style_guide.md`\n29: - `references/opencode/typescript/quality_standards.md`\n30: - `references/opencode/typescript/quick_reference.md`\n31: - `references/opencode/shared/code_organization.md`\n32: - `references/opencode/shared/universal_patterns.md`\n33: \n34: **Expected assets loaded**:\n35: - `assets/opencode/checklists/typescript_checklist.md`\n36: - `assets/opencode/checklists/universal_checklist.md`\n37: \n38: **Expected NOT loaded**: any of `references/opencode/{python,shell,config}/*`, any of `assets/opencode/checklists/{python,shell,config}_checklist.md`.\n39: \n40: ## 3. TEST EXECUTION\n41: \n42: ### Preconditions\n43: \n44: 1. Target file exists: `bash: test -f .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts`\n45: 2. TypeScript sub-language reference set intact: `bash: ls .opencode/skills/sk-code/references/opencode/typescript/ | sort` returns exactly `quality_standards.md style_guide.md quick_reference.md` (in some sort order).\n46: \n47: ### Exact Command Sequence\n48: \n49: 1. **Invoke sk-code** with the prompt.\n50: 2. **Capture loaded refs** to `/tmp/skc-LS001-loaded-refs.txt`.\n51: 3. **Verify**: 3 typescript/* + 2 shared/* refs loaded; 0 python/shell/config refs loaded.\n52: \n53: ### Pass/Fail Criteria\n54: \n55: - **PASS** iff: exactly 3 typescript/* refs + 2 shared/* refs in load set AND 0 other-sub-language refs.\n56: - **FAIL** iff: any python/shell/config sub-language ref is loaded, OR fewer than 3 typescript/* refs loaded.\n57: \n58: ### Failure Triage\n59: \n60: 1. If a python/shell/config ref leaks: verify the file extension parsing in SKILL.md sub-detection table.\n61: 2. If quick_reference.md is missing: check whether the quick-reference always-load rule in `resource_loading.md` is intact.\n62: \n63: ## 4. SOURCE FILES\n64: \n65: - `.opencode/skills/sk-code/SKILL.md` (lines 78-90 — sub-detection table).\n66: - `.opencode/skills/sk-code/references/stack_detection.md` (lines 50-62).\n67: - `.opencode/skills/sk-code/references/opencode/typescript/{style_guide,quality_standards,quick_reference}.md`.\n68: \n69: ## 5. SOURCE METADATA\n70: \n71: - **Created**: 2026-05-04\n72: - **Critical path**: No\n73: - **Destructive**: No\n74: - **Concurrent-safe**: Yes\n75: - **Last validated**: pending first manual run\n\n(End of file - total 75 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"LS-001: OPENCODE TypeScript Sub-Detection\"\ndescription: \"Verify that within OPENCODE surface, TypeScript file extensions trigger loading of typescript/* references (not python, shell, or config).\"\n---\n\n# LS-001: OPENCODE TypeScript Sub-Detection\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThis scenario verifies the language sub-detection layer within OPENCODE. When the target file extension is `.ts`, `.tsx`, `.mts`, or `.d.ts`, sk-code MUST load the `references/opencode/typescript/*` set and corresponding `assets/opencode/checklists/typescript_checklist.md`, while excluding python, shell, and config sub-language references.\n\nSub-detection rules are defined in SKILL.md lines 78-90 and `references/stack_detection.md:50-62`.\n\n## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n\n**Realistic user request**: A maintainer wants to harden the executor-config parser to throw early when an invalid model is supplied for cli-codex.\n\n**Exact prompt**:\n```\nRefactor the parseExecutorConfig function in .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts to throw on missing model when type is cli-codex.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/02--language-sub-detection/004-opencode-typescript.md","time":{"start":1780373179932,"end":1780373179951}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_04711fd250ccd945016a1e56bbcd7c8191b43e37b6f39a528c"}},"id":"prt_e8682cdf300176XIlc05VHHbNl","sessionID":"ses_1797e0d22ffeXZXWmRS3UmbrPG","messageID":"msg_e8682affc0017thL0dq1w8C6yZ"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780373179955,"sessionID":"ses_1797e0d22ffeXZXWmRS3UmbrPG","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_jGeBDTgXYPXkIfBvvJvHhdd7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/02--language-sub-detection/005-opencode-python.md","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/02--language-sub-detection/005-opencode-python.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"LS-002: OPENCODE Python Sub-Detection\"\n3: description: \"Verify that within OPENCODE surface, Python file extensions trigger loading of python/* references (not typescript, shell, or config).\"\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # LS-002: OPENCODE Python Sub-Detection\n7: \n8: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n9: \n10: Verify language sub-detection for `.py` files within OPENCODE surface. The Python ref set MUST load; TypeScript/Shell/Config sets MUST NOT.\n11: \n12: Sub-detection rules defined in SKILL.md lines 78-90.\n13: \n14: ## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n15: \n16: **Realistic user request**: Add a `--json-output` flag to the skill advisor CLI for machine-readable results.\n17: \n18: **Exact prompt**:\n19: ```\n20: Update the skill_advisor.py argparse block at .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py to add a --json-output flag that emits results as JSON.\n21: ```\n22: \n23: **Expected detection**:\n24: - Surface: `OPENCODE`\n25: - Sub-language: `PYTHON` (target file `.py`, also Python-specific signal: `argparse`)\n26: \n27: **Expected references loaded**:\n28: - `references/opencode/python/style_guide.md`\n29: - `references/opencode/python/quality_standards.md`\n30: - `references/opencode/python/quick_reference.md`\n31: - `references/opencode/shared/code_organization.md`\n32: - `references/opencode/shared/universal_patterns.md`\n33: \n34: **Expected assets loaded**:\n35: - `assets/opencode/checklists/python_checklist.md`\n36: - `assets/opencode/checklists/universal_checklist.md`\n37: \n38: **Expected NOT loaded**: any of `references/opencode/{typescript,shell,config}/*`.\n39: \n40: ## 3. TEST EXECUTION\n41: \n42: ### Preconditions\n43: \n44: 1. Target file exists: `bash: test -f .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py`\n45: 2. Python sub-language reference set intact: 3 files under `references/opencode/python/`.\n46: \n47: ### Exact Command Sequence\n48: \n49: 1. Invoke sk-code with the prompt.\n50: 2. Capture loaded refs to `/tmp/skc-LS002-loaded-refs.txt`.\n51: 3. Verify: 3 python/* + 2 shared/* refs loaded; 0 typescript/shell/config refs.\n52: \n53: ### Pass/Fail Criteria\n54: \n55: - **PASS** iff: 3 python/* refs + 2 shared/* refs loaded AND 0 other-sub-language refs.\n56: - **FAIL** iff: any typescript/shell/config ref leaks, OR fewer than 3 python/* refs loaded.\n57: \n58: ### Failure Triage\n59: \n60: 1. If a typescript/* ref leaks: the extension detector is mis-firing on the `.py` extension.\n61: 2. If python signals not detected: verify `argparse`, `pytest`, `def `, docstring patterns in SKILL.md sub-detection table.\n62: \n63: ## 4. SOURCE FILES\n64: \n65: - `.opencode/skills/sk-code/SKILL.md` (sub-detection table).\n66: - `.opencode/skills/sk-code/references/opencode/python/{style_guide,quality_standards,quick_reference}.md`.\n67: \n68: ## 5. SOURCE METADATA\n69: \n70: - **Created**: 2026-05-04\n71: - **Critical path**: No\n72: - **Destructive**: No\n73: - **Concurrent-safe**: Yes\n74: - **Last validated**: pending first manual run\n\n(End of file - total 74 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"LS-002: OPENCODE Python Sub-Detection\"\ndescription: \"Verify that within OPENCODE surface, Python file extensions trigger loading of python/* references (not typescript, shell, or config).\"\n---\n\n# LS-002: OPENCODE Python Sub-Detection\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nVerify language sub-detection for `.py` files within OPENCODE surface. The Python ref set MUST load; TypeScript/Shell/Config sets MUST NOT.\n\nSub-detection rules defined in SKILL.md lines 78-90.\n\n## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n\n**Realistic user request**: Add a `--json-output` flag to the skill advisor CLI for machine-readable results.\n\n**Exact prompt**:\n```\nUpdate the skill_advisor.py argparse block at .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py to add a --json-output flag that emits results as JSON.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/02--language-sub-detection/005-opencode-python.md","time":{"start":1780373179937,"end":1780373179953}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_04711fd250ccd945016a1e56bbcd88819183f8221032288dce"}},"id":"prt_e8682ce1e001tMny0rdCGx04dI","sessionID":"ses_1797e0d22ffeXZXWmRS3UmbrPG","messageID":"msg_e8682affc0017thL0dq1w8C6yZ"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780373179955,"sessionID":"ses_1797e0d22ffeXZXWmRS3UmbrPG","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_hLh9Zn3L5RD8PbPbIElyfedT","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/02--language-sub-detection/006-opencode-shell.md","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/02--language-sub-detection/006-opencode-shell.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"LS-003: OPENCODE Shell Sub-Detection\"\n3: description: \"Verify that within OPENCODE surface, shell-script extensions trigger loading of shell/* references (not typescript, python, or config).\"\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # LS-003: OPENCODE Shell Sub-Detection\n7: \n8: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n9: \n10: Verify language sub-detection for `.sh` / `.bash` files within OPENCODE. Shell ref set loads; TypeScript/Python/Config sets do not.\n11: \n12: ## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n13: \n14: **Realistic user request**: Harden a validation script with strict mode and a cleanup trap.\n15: \n16: **Exact prompt**:\n17: ```\n18: Add set -euo pipefail and a trap to .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh to clean up the temp dir on exit.\n19: ```\n20: \n21: **Expected detection**:\n22: - Surface: `OPENCODE`\n23: - Sub-language: `SHELL` (target `.sh`, signals: `set -euo pipefail`, `trap`)\n24: \n25: **Expected references loaded**:\n26: - `references/opencode/shell/style_guide.md`\n27: - `references/opencode/shell/quality_standards.md`\n28: - `references/opencode/shell/quick_reference.md`\n29: - `references/opencode/shared/code_organization.md`\n30: - `references/opencode/shared/universal_patterns.md`\n31: \n32: **Expected assets loaded**:\n33: - `assets/opencode/checklists/shell_checklist.md`\n34: - `assets/opencode/checklists/universal_checklist.md`\n35: \n36: **Expected NOT loaded**: any `references/opencode/{typescript,python,config}/*`.\n37: \n38: ## 3. TEST EXECUTION\n39: \n40: ### Preconditions\n41: \n42: 1. Target file exists: `bash: test -f .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh`\n43: 2. Shell sub-language reference set intact: 3 files under `references/opencode/shell/`.\n44: \n45: ### Exact Command Sequence\n46: \n47: 1. Invoke sk-code with the prompt.\n48: 2. Capture loaded refs to `/tmp/skc-LS003-loaded-refs.txt`.\n49: 3. Verify: 3 shell/* + 2 shared/* refs loaded; 0 typescript/python/config refs.\n50: \n51: ### Pass/Fail Criteria\n52: \n53: - **PASS** iff: 3 shell/* refs + 2 shared/* refs loaded AND 0 other-sub-language refs.\n54: - **FAIL** iff: any typescript/python/config ref leaks.\n55: \n56: ### Failure Triage\n57: \n58: 1. Verify `.sh` and shebang signals (`#!/bin/bash`, `#!/usr/bin/env bash`) in SKILL.md sub-detection table.\n59: 2. Verify `pipefail` is in the SHELL signal keywords list.\n60: \n61: ## 4. SOURCE FILES\n62: \n63: - `.opencode/skills/sk-code/SKILL.md` (sub-detection table).\n64: - `.opencode/skills/sk-code/references/opencode/shell/{style_guide,quality_standards,quick_reference}.md`.\n65: \n66: ## 5. SOURCE METADATA\n67: \n68: - **Created**: 2026-05-04\n69: - **Critical path**: No\n70: - **Destructive**: No\n71: - **Concurrent-safe**: Yes\n72: - **Last validated**: pending first manual run\n\n(End of file - total 72 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"LS-003: OPENCODE Shell Sub-Detection\"\ndescription: \"Verify that within OPENCODE surface, shell-script extensions trigger loading of shell/* references (not typescript, python, or config).\"\n---\n\n# LS-003: OPENCODE Shell Sub-Detection\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nVerify language sub-detection for `.sh` / `.bash` files within OPENCODE. Shell ref set loads; TypeScript/Python/Config sets do not.\n\n## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n\n**Realistic user request**: Harden a validation script with strict mode and a cleanup trap.\n\n**Exact prompt**:\n```\nAdd set -euo pipefail and a trap to .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh to clean up the temp dir on exit.\n```\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/02--language-sub-detection/006-opencode-shell.md","time":{"start":1780373179942,"end":1780373179954}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_04711fd250ccd945016a1e56bbcd908191bfa299a5d44374f5"}},"id":"prt_e8682ce23001UuYEapcB4ImBL5","sessionID":"ses_1797e0d22ffeXZXWmRS3UmbrPG","messageID":"msg_e8682affc0017thL0dq1w8C6yZ"}}
